Enemies who try to attack Iran will face defeat, a senior Iranian military official said on Tuesday, after the United States, Saudi Arabia and European powers accused the Islamic republic of carrying out an attack on Saudi oil facilities. “We have repeatedly told the enemy that if there is any violation toward this country, they will face the same action that took place with the American drone and the English tanker,” Iran’s armed forces chief of staff, Major General Mohammad Baqeri, said, according to the Tasnim news agency. “The result of a violation toward this country will be captivity and defeat.” Vanguard News Nigeria. An attack on Saudi Arabia that shut 5 per cent of global crude output caused the biggest surge in oil prices since 1991 after U.S. officials blamed Iran and President Donald Trump said Washington was “locked and loaded” to retaliate. September 16, 2019 In "Foreign" Iran’s military chief said on a visit to Damascus on Wednesday that it was unacceptable for Israel to violate Syrian air space and land “any time it wants”. October 18, 2017 In "News" Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on Monday new United States sanctions, under which Iran’s central bank was blacklisted for a second time, pointed to US “desperation” in face of the Iranian resistance. The United States on Friday imposed another round of sanctions on Iran, including on its central bank which… September 23, 2019 In "Foreign"